Definition: the usage or vocabulary that is characteristic of a specific group of people
Example: the immigrants spoke an odd dialect of English; he has a strong German accent; it has been said that a language is a dialect with an army and navy
Synonyms: adj, pert, dialectal, idiom, accent, verb, communication, accentuate, non-standard_speech, the, usage, or, vocabulary, that, is, characteristic, of, a, specific, group, people, immigrants, spoke, an, odd, English, he, has, strong, German, it, been, said, language, with, army, and, navy
Category: noun.communication
